q3 difference between tag, element and attribute
<!--
Tag:
A tag is written inside angle brackets.
Example: <p>

Element:
An element includes opening tag, content, and closing tag.
Example: <p>Hello</p>

Attribute:
An attribute gives extra information to a tag.
Example: href in <a href="https://google.com">
-->
q4 difference between block-level <div> and inline elements <span>
<!--
<div> is a block-level element.
It takes full width and starts from a new line.

<span> is an inline element.
It only takes required width and stays in same line.

<div> is used for webpage sections/layout.
<span> is used for styling small text parts.
-->
q5 why you always add rel="noopener noreferrer" when using target="_blank"?
 What security risk does it prevent?
<!--
rel="noopener noreferrer" is used with target="_blank".

It improves security and prevents the new webpage
from accessing or controlling the original webpage.
-->
